The paper focuses on solving the problem of max-kernel search efficiently, which is a problem commonly encountered in machine learning and computer vision applications. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories. Additionally, the paper mentions empirical results for data sets and abstract objects, indicating that it may also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper presents a method for indexing objects in a Hilbert space, which may be of interest to researchers in cs.IT (Information Theory).
